    {
      "id": "text-253",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 1574,
      "width": 3360,
      "height": 486,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#495057",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 46169,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 46169,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "\u2022  DEDUP map (multiple subsystems referenced the same node under different ids): trait-game=core-game-trait; trait-evaluator=core-evaluator-\n   trait; trait-encoder=core-encoder-trait; search-core=core-search; arena-core=core-arena; core-net / net-evaluator=core-net-evaluator;\n   core-checkers=checkers-glue; core-books=wallchess-books; core-features=wallchess-features; wasm-crate=wasm-bridge; wasm-pkg=wasm-bundle-\n   engine; core-lib re-exports folded into the L2 seam nodes.\n\u2022  TT + killers/history + pruning bundle + qsearch were merged into one L2 node (core-search-internals) to keep the engine band readable; in\n   source they are all in core/src/search.rs gated by SearchConfig flags (Default = LMR+TT only = previously deployed engine).\n\u2022  THE SEAM: everything in L2 except core-graph/core-mcts/core-net-evaluator is generic over Game; Search keeps a single type param\n   E:Evaluator and reaches its game via E::G. Proven by two games (WallChess + Checkers) sharing Search/arena with zero game-specific search\n   code (bin/checkers.rs).\n\u2022  PLAY flow (top-down): webui game route -> api.ts -> WASM engine bundle (choose_move/analyze, Gen-2 =\n   Heuristic::new(50,120,true)+SearchConfig::aggressive). Net path -> WASM net bundle NetBot (candle) is DASHED: off-by-default, not in the\n   deployed 137KB bundle.\n\u2022  TRAIN flow (bottom band): data-gen CLIs -> data/*.jsonl -> dataset.py -> train.py/distill.py -> *.safetensors -> copied to public +\n   loaded by NetEvaluator (candle). Deployed weight = wallnet-v6-512h (512-hidden MLP).\n\u2022  ENCODING PARITY is the load-bearing cross-language contract (dashed edge encoding.py -> wc features): Rust core/src/{action,features}.rs\n   == trainer/encoding.py == TS api.ts index<->move. WallChess FEATURE_LEN=300, ACTION_COUNT=209 (trainer/README.md says 293 and is STALE).\n\u2022  DEFERRED (role:deferred, dashed edges): (1) MCTS/PolicyValue genericization over Game (core-mcts-generic-deferred) \u2014 Encoder is already\n   generic, PolicyValue is not, deferred until checkers NN training begins; (2) games/ subdir nesting (phase-3 relocate, rules still flat at\n   crate root); (3) WASM net bundle / NetBot in-browser (off-by-default net feature); (4) Checkers trainer + webui + wasm (checkers-trainer-\n   deferred) \u2014 no checkers in trainer/, webui/, data/, or wasm DTOs.\n\u2022  STILL WALLCHESS-BOUND inside the generic engine band (not generic): core-mcts (mcts.rs PolicyValue+Mcts+HeuristicPolicy), core-net-\n   evaluator (net.rs, feature=net), and core-graph (lib.rs analyze/top_moves/generate_graph glue predating the Game trait).\n\u2022  Checkers is a single flat file (core/src/checkers.rs) \u2014 split into L4 nodes (state/neighbor/movegen/encoder/perft) for the diagram; tests\n   are the only nested child (core/src/checkers/tests.rs). Checkers has no books / no opening book / no immediate_winning_move and no\n   interior move pruning (search_moves == legal_moves).\n\u2022  Crate is gameboard-core (lib gameboard_core); wasm package is still named wallchess-wasm (ground truth, not yet renamed). bestmove.rs\n   defines the cross-binary 'bestmove protocol' consumed by xmatch as referee (enables new-vs-old search matches without rebuilding).",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\u2022  DEDUP map (multiple subsystems referenced the same node under different ids): trait-game=core-game-trait; trait-evaluator=core-evaluator-\n   trait; trait-encoder=core-encoder-trait; search-core=core-search; arena-core=core-arena; core-net / net-evaluator=core-net-evaluator;\n   core-checkers=checkers-glue; core-books=wallchess-books; core-features=wallchess-features; wasm-crate=wasm-bridge; wasm-pkg=wasm-bundle-\n   engine; core-lib re-exports folded into the L2 seam nodes.\n\u2022  TT + killers/history + pruning bundle + qsearch were merged into one L2 node (core-search-internals) to keep the engine band readable; in\n   source they are all in core/src/search.rs gated by SearchConfig flags (Default = LMR+TT only = previously deployed engine).\n\u2022  THE SEAM: everything in L2 except core-graph/core-mcts/core-net-evaluator is generic over Game; Search keeps a single type param\n   E:Evaluator and reaches its game via E::G. Proven by two games (WallChess + Checkers) sharing Search/arena with zero game-specific search\n   code (bin/checkers.rs).\n\u2022  PLAY flow (top-down): webui game route -> api.ts -> WASM engine bundle (choose_move/analyze, Gen-2 =\n   Heuristic::new(50,120,true)+SearchConfig::aggressive). Net path -> WASM net bundle NetBot (candle) is DASHED: off-by-default, not in the\n   deployed 137KB bundle.\n\u2022  TRAIN flow (bottom band): data-gen CLIs -> data/*.jsonl -> dataset.py -> train.py/distill.py -> *.safetensors -> copied to public +\n   loaded by NetEvaluator (candle). Deployed weight = wallnet-v6-512h (512-hidden MLP).\n\u2022  ENCODING PARITY is the load-bearing cross-language contract (dashed edge encoding.py -> wc features): Rust core/src/{action,features}.rs\n   == trainer/encoding.py == TS api.ts index<->move. WallChess FEATURE_LEN=300, ACTION_COUNT=209 (trainer/README.md says 293 and is STALE).\n\u2022  DEFERRED (role:deferred, dashed edges): (1) MCTS/PolicyValue genericization over Game (core-mcts-generic-deferred) \u2014 Encoder is already\n   generic, PolicyValue is not, deferred until checkers NN training begins; (2) games/ subdir nesting (phase-3 relocate, rules still flat at\n   crate root); (3) WASM net bundle / NetBot in-browser (off-by-default net feature); (4) Checkers trainer + webui + wasm (checkers-trainer-\n   deferred) \u2014 no checkers in trainer/, webui/, data/, or wasm DTOs.\n\u2022  STILL WALLCHESS-BOUND inside the generic engine band (not generic): core-mcts (mcts.rs PolicyValue+Mcts+HeuristicPolicy), core-net-\n   evaluator (net.rs, feature=net), and core-graph (lib.rs analyze/top_moves/generate_graph glue predating the Game trait).\n\u2022  Checkers is a single flat file (core/src/checkers.rs) \u2014 split into L4 nodes (state/neighbor/movegen/encoder/perft) for the diagram; tests\n   are the only nested child (core/src/checkers/tests.rs). Checkers has no books / no opening book / no immediate_winning_move and no\n   interior move pruning (search_moves == legal_moves).\n\u2022  Crate is gameboard-core (lib gameboard_core); wasm package is still named wallchess-wasm (ground truth, not yet renamed). bestmove.rs\n   defines the cross-binary 'bestmove protocol' consumed by xmatch as referee (enables new-vs-old search matches without rebuilding).",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
